âœ… When to Use ping:
Check if a website or server is up.

Test your internet connection.

Diagnose network delays or packet loss.

Find issues with local or remote network connectivity.


| Command                  | Description                        |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------------------- |
| `ping -n 5 google.com`   | Send 5 ping requests               |
| `ping -l 100 google.com` | Send ping with 100 bytes of data   |
| `ping -t google.com`     | Ping continuously (Ctrl+C to stop) |
| `ping -4 google.com`     | Force IPv4 ping                    |
| `ping -6 google.com`     | Force IPv6 ping                    |
